' FreeCAD <-> Gazebo via MCP — sequence: human in Simulation Workbench
' Part of freecad_gazebo_mcp_*.puml set

@startuml sequence_human_in_workbench
title Human-driven flow — user clicks Play in the Simulation Workbench

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

actor       User
participant "FreeCAD GUI"           as GUI
participant "Simulation\nWorkbench" as WB
participant "RobotCAD"              as RC
database    "Repo"                  as Repo
participant "gz-sim -s\n(headless)" as Sim

== Switch workspace (Fusion-style) ==
User -> GUI : switch to\nSimulation Workbench
GUI --> User : toolbars + panels swap

== Load scenario ==
User -> WB  : pick world + robot +\ninitial pose, click "Start"
WB   -> RC  : ensure URDF/SDF\nis up to date
RC   -> Repo: write generated/ if stale
WB   -> Sim : start, load world, spawn robot
Sim  --> WB : ready

== Run with live feedback in FreeCAD ==
User -> WB  : click ▶ Play
WB   -> Sim : unpause
loop every tick (~30 Hz)
  Sim --> WB : pose, joint state, sensors
  WB  -> GUI : update Placement on FreeCAD\nobjects (animate the model)
  WB  -> WB  : render camera frame in\nQt panel, append to plots
end

== Pause & inspect ==
User -> WB  : click ⏸ Pause
WB   -> Sim : pause
User -> GUI : orbit / measure /\ntweak parameter
note right of GUI
  Same FreeCAD doc, same 3D view.
  No Gazebo window ever appears.
end note

== Save the run ==
User -> WB  : click "Save run"
WB   -> Sim : stop record
WB   -> Repo: write sim_runs/<timestamp>/
WB   --> User: run saved, listed in Run Library

@enduml
